id: pm-3299
title: pm-changelog over-escapes markdown in entry titles (parens + intra-word underscores)
description: "PR #301 review (Gemini, Sourcery) flagged that auto-generated CHANGELOG.md entries contain unnecessary markdown backslash escapes, e.g. escaped underscores in EXTENSION_AUTHOR_CONTRACTS and escaped parentheses around '(actual 1.4.0)'. These come from pm-changelog's title-escaping pass. On GitHub-flavored markdown, intra-word underscores do not trigger emphasis and parentheses are not special outside link syntax, so the escapes are unnecessary (they render correctly on GitHub but add source noise). Fix belongs in the SEPARATE pm-changelog repo (sibling checkout), NOT pm-cli: relax the escaper to only escape characters that are actually markdown-significant in the entry context. Cannot be hand-fixed in CHANGELOG.md here because changelog:pm:check regenerates and would re-add the escapes."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 4
tags[4]: "area:changelog",docs,pm-changelog,upstream
created_at: "2026-06-19T13:54:21.639Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-20T03:27:21.246Z"
author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: "pm-changelog no longer escapes ( ) and intra-word _ in generated entry titles; a regenerated pm-cli CHANGELOG.md has clean entries and changelog:pm:check still passes; pm-changelog gains a unit test for the escaping rule."
parent: pm-u9d0
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-20T03:15:46.335Z",codex-implementation-agent,"Evidence: upstream pm-changelog fix implemented under pmc-8t9f and dependency audit cleanup under pmc-licw. Local patched pm-changelog CLI generated pm-cli changelog output with clean 'EXTENSION_AUTHOR_CONTRACTS' and '(actual 1.4.0)' title text and no escaped underscore/parenthesis matches. Current pm-cli CHANGELOG remains unchanged until the upstream package is released and consumed via pnpm changelog:pm."
  "2026-06-20T03:25:30.054Z",codex-implementation-agent,"Evidence: direct real-repo pnpm changelog:pm:check passed after installing pm-changelog@2026.6.20. Removed it from linked-test execution because pm linked tests sandbox PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH, while changelog:pm:check intentionally compares the real repository CHANGELOG.md against real tracker state."
  "2026-06-20T03:27:19.947Z",codex-implementation-agent,"Closure evidence: upstream pm-changelog PR #50 merged and released as pm-changelog@2026.6.20; downstream installed latest package, regenerated CHANGELOG.md with clean EXTENSION_AUTHOR_CONTRACTS and (actual 1.4.0) entries, verified direct pnpm changelog:pm:check, linked test run passed, npm/dependabot audit clean, security scan clean, build passed, Sentry/telemetry gate returned 0 critical and 0 high issues."
